 <blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="padding-left:1ex;margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;border-left:#ccc 1px solid">Okay, I fixed this today too....r21219 <div>  <div><br><br><br>On May 11, 2009, at 11:27 PM, Anton Starikov wrote:<br>
<br> <blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="padding-left:1ex;margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;border-left:#ccc 1px solid">Now there is another problem :)<br><br>You can try oversubscribe node. At least by 1 task.<br>If you hostfile and rank file limit you at N procs, you can ask mpirun for N+1 and it wil be not rejected.<br>
 Although in reality there will be N tasks.<br>So, if your hostfile limit is 4, then &quot;mpirun -np 4&quot; and &quot;mpirun -np 5&quot; both works, but in both cases there are only 4 tasks. It isn&#39;t crucial, because there is nor real oversubscription, but there is still some bug which can affect something in future.<br>
